Another lesson learned: Be fearful of the merchants of attention in the business media that almost universally parade in a bullish costume. "First level thinking," the absence of rigorous analysis and "group stink" are all harmful to your investment well being. Stay independent

and rigorous in approach and avoid indicators (e.g. unusual call activity and a quick look at a chart) that are used to hook retail investors (to buy a service) and make things seem easier than they are in selecting equities.
The investment mosaic is complicated and the past (trend(s)) are not the sole factor to making invt/trading decisions. If they were librarians would be the wealthiest investors in the world.
